    "plan_content": "## Implementation Plan: Atomic Model Rename\n\nHere's what I found in the codebase and what needs to be done across **4 files** in **7 precise edits**:\n\n---\n\n### Files to Modify\n\n| File | Change |\n|---|---|\n| `api/types.go` | Add `RenameRequest` struct |\n| `api/client.go` | Add `Client.Rename()` method |\n| `server/routes.go` | Add `RenameHandler` + register `/api/rename` route |\n| `cmd/cmd.go` | Add `RenameHandler` func + `renameCmd` + register in `AddCommand` |\n\n---\n\n### Step-by-step\n\n**Step 1 — `api/types.go`** (after line 765, after `CopyRequest`)\nAdd `RenameRequest` with `Source`/`Destination` string fields and `json:\"source\"`/`json:\"destination\"` tags — exact mirror of `CopyRequest`.\n\n**Step 2 — `api/client.go`** (after line 387, after `Client.Copy()`)\nAdd `Rename(ctx, *RenameRequest) error` calling `c.do(ctx, http.MethodPost, \"/api/rename\", req, nil)` — exact mirror of `Copy()`.\n\n**Step 3 — `server/routes.go`** (after line 1483, after `CopyHandler`)\nAdd `RenameHandler` with this flow:\n1. Bind JSON → 400 on missing body\n2. Validate non-empty `Source`/`Destination` → 400\n3. `model.ParseName()` + `IsValid()` on both → 400 with `errtypes.InvalidModelNameErrMsg`\n4. `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(dst)` — if **no error** → **409 Conflict** (\"destination model 'X' already exists\")\n5. `CopyModel(src, dst)` → 404 on `os.ErrNotExist`, 500 otherwise\n6. `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(src)` → `m.Remove()` → `m.RemoveLayers()` → 500 on failure\n7. Return **200** `{\"status\": \"success\"}`\n\n**Step 4 — `server/routes.go`** (line 1698, after `/api/copy`)\nAdd `r.POST(\"/api/rename\", s.RenameHandler)`.\n\n**Step 5 — `cmd/cmd.go`** (after line 1350, after `CopyHandler`)\nAdd `RenameHandler` func: creates client, calls `client.Rename()`, prints `Renamed \"SOURCE\" to \"DESTINATION\"`.\n\n**Step 6 — `cmd/cmd.go`** (after line 2263, after `copyCmd`)\nAdd `renameCmd` with `Use: \"rename SOURCE DESTINATION\"`, `Short: \"Rename a model\"`, `Args: cobra.ExactArgs(2)`, `PreRunE: checkServerHeartbeat`, `RunE: RenameHandler`.\n\n**Step 7 — `cmd/cmd.go`** (line 2345, in `rootCmd.AddCommand`)\nInsert `renameCmd` between `copyCmd` and `deleteCmd`.\n\n---\n\n**No new imports are needed** — all required packages (`manifest`, `model`, `errtypes`, `os`, `fmt`, `errors`, `http`, `gin`) are already imported in their respective files.",
